  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it elapsed, you know, from September 1945 till 1946 December.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We arrive in the Belgian Congo.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But before that we arrive, you know, there, we have to go-- we have to go to Rome and to take the passport.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To take the passport, because only there they give passport to be made for desperate people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had the passport, and the ticket, and all collected.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went by train to Belgian-- to Brussels.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because, at the time, you know, after the war, Brussels was the only country, as yet, you know, this colony, who had, you know, these yellow-- yellow-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you know, yellow sickness vaccination.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They didn't exist nowhere in the world.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And also, to have vaccination against the sickness of the sleep.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, in the-- a long time ago, in the Belgian Congo, there were all these tsetse flies and all these that we bring you disease, you know.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, you can sleep.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you can sleep forever, you die.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when you come there, it was, you know, it was the compulsory to have those vaccination-- one against the yellow fever and tsetse fly above the [FRENCH].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They call it [FRENCH] in French.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It means the sickness of sleeping.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, once, we have to-- and then, you know, not only you have to be vaccinated, you have to--",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] It want to be vaccinated, you see.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- we stayed there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not only when you had this vaccination, you have to know that the vaccination has been positive-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] Vaccination has been positive.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
